sample.title: Waymo Leads The 2025 Robotaxi Surge As Zoox Expands And Tesla Races To Catch Up
sample.description:
Alphabet-owned Waymo scaled up and now leads the American robotaxi market by far, while Baidu-owned Apollo Go dominated in China. In the San Francisco Bay Area, there are now multiple robotaxi services operating, including Zoox and Waymo, although only Waymo provides commercial rides completely free of any human safety operators. Tesla finally launched their robotaxis in Austin and San Francisco but both states include human safety supervisors onboard ready to quickly take over driving. In December, Musk confirmed that driverless robotaxi tests had begun in Austin, which drove Tesla stock to a year high.

sample.title: How to 'invest in' private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX
sample.description:
Private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX have captured enormous investor enthusiasm, driving up their valuations. Yet because they‚Äôre privately held, they‚Äôve remained largely inaccessible to retail investors.

Now a new approached called tokenization could change that by giving retail investors access to investments aligned with the performance of private companies. But some worry that tokenizing private companies could be a way to bypass longstanding regulations meant to protect investors.

sample.title: Why U.S. Shipbuilding Collapsed ‚Äî And The Push To Rebuild It
sample.description:
America used to be a world leader in shipbuilding. But with a shortage of talent, antiquated operating procedures and outdated facilities the industry ‚Äî essential to U.S. energy security and defense ‚Äî is in crisis. China dominates the global commercial shipbuilding industry accounting for 53% of global market share followed by South Korea and Japan. The U.S. accounts for about 0.1%. But that could soon change. In southern Philadelphia, $5 billion is being invested by South Korean shipping conglomerate Hanwha. It hopes to turn this decades old shipyard into a state of the art facility. To look at how shipyards are being revitalized, CNBC traveled to Wisconsin‚Äôs Great Lakes region and to one of America's oldest shipyards in Philadelphia.

sample.description:
What can we expect from the Epstein files release? | BBC News

Friday 19 December is the legal deadline for the US department of justice to release its files pertaining to its investigations into late convicted sex offender and financier Jeffrey Epstein.

At various stages over the years, some materials have been put into the public domain. The contents of the unreleased documents remain unknown.

The files will be released on Friday - except for those that relate to an active criminal investigation, identify victims of Epstein's abuse or invade their privacy, or contain images of physical and child sex abuse, death, or injury.

sample.title: ‚ÄòRockstar Games fired me over alleged leaks - I just wanted to join a union‚Äô | BBC News
sample.description:
Jack Hoxby was one of 31 employees dismissed by Rockstar North in October for gross misconduct.
 
Jack and some of the other employees were accused of being behind leaks of Rockstar projects, but the employees allege it was because they wanted to join a union.
 
In an interview with BBC Newsbeat, Jack discusses the fact it was a dream job, and all he would want is to have it back, but it's important for people in the industry to be able to join a union.
 
Rockstar North said it was incorrect to suggest the dismissals were linked to union membership or activities. It said it took action after staff discussed confidential information, including specific game features from upcoming titles, in a public forum.

sample.title: EU agrees ‚Ç¨90bn loan for Ukraine but without using Russian assets | BBC News
sample.description:
European Union leaders have struck a deal to give Ukraine a ‚Ç¨90bn (¬£79bn; $105bn) loan after failing to agree on using frozen Russian assets.
 
The agreement, which leaders said would meet Ukraine's military and economic needs for the next two years, came after more than a day of talks at a summit in Brussels.
 
"We committed, we delivered," EU chief Antonio Costa wrote on X as he announced the deal to provide a loan backed by the bloc's common budget.
 
Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky said the support "truly strengthens our resilience", adding that Russian assets should remain "immobilised".
 
Meanwhile, Russian envoy Kirill Dmitriev said the decision not to use frozen Russian assets is a "major blow to EU warmongers" and adds "law and sanity win‚Ä¶ for now".

sample.title: Brown University shooting suspect found dead, police say | BBC News
sample.description:
The suspect ‚Äçin ‚Äãlast week's ‚Äåmass shooting at Brown University has been found dead in a storage facility in Salem, New Hampshire, following a six-day multi-state manhunt, police say.

They identified the suspect as Claudio Neves Valente, 48, a Portuguese national who studied at the university in Providence, Rhode Island, about 25 years ago.

Providence police chief Oscar Perez said video evidence and tips from the public led investigators to a car-rental location where they found the suspect's name and matched him to their person of interest.

Officials said they also believe Valente killed a Massachusetts Institute of Technology professor two days after the 13 December shooting at Brown.
